description: This module defines an extension to the NETCONF protocol that allows the NETCONF client to control how default values are handled by the server in particular NETCONF operations. Possible modes to report default data.
All default data is reported. Any nodes considered to be default data will contain a 'default' XML attribute, set to 'true' or '1'.
Values are not reported if they contain the default.
Report values that contain the definition of explicitly set data.
Contains the <with-defaults> parameter for control of defaults in NETCONF retrieval operations.
The explicit defaults processing mode requested.
